sentences: Mariana Sadovska (born 1972, Lviv, Ukraine) is a Ukrainian actress, singer, musician, recording artist, and composer, resident in Cologne.

In 2001, she moved to New York with a grant from the Earth Foundation.
In 2001, Global Village produced her first solo CD, Songs I learned in Ukraine.
In 2005, Sadovska and EVOE group produced her second solo CD Borderland.
In July 2005, she taught workshops at the University of Kabul (Afghanistan).
In 2006 she was a guest musical director for the Art Atelier Program curated by Toni Morrison at Princeton University.
In 2008 Sadovska became a Fulbright scholar.
